Name: ret_60_12
definition: ratio of change of cumulative stock returns 1 year lagged  from to cumulative stock returns 5 years lagged

Name: ret_3_1
definition: ratio of cumulative stock returns from the previous month to the cumulative stock returns lagged 3 months (i.e. 3 months ago).

Name: ret_6_1
definition: ratio of cumulative stock returns from the previous month to the cumulative stock returns lagged 6 months (i.e. 6 months ago).

Name: ret_12_7
definition: ratio of cumulative stock returns lagged 7 months to the cumulative stock  stock returns lagged 1 year (i.e 1 year ago).

Name: ret_12_1
definition: ratio of cumulative stock returns from the previous month to the cumulative stock returns lagged 1 year (i.e 1 year ago).

Name: ret_9_1
definition: ratio of cumulative stock returns from the previous month to the cumulative stock returns lagged 9 months (i.e. 9 months ago).

Name: ret_1_0
definition: ratio of the current Cumulative stock return estimated from stock returns to the Cumulative stock return estimated from stock returns lagged 1 month.

Name: iskew_capm_21d
definition: Idiosyncratic skewness from the CAPM model (skewness of the error term of the CAPM model)

Name: iskew_ff3_21d
definition: Idiosyncratic skewness from the Fama-French 3-factor model (skewness of the error term of the Fama-French 3-factor model)

Name: beta_60m
definition: CAPM (i.e. Capital Asset Pricing Model) Beta  (i.e. measure of the volatility–or systematic risk–of a security or portfolio compared to the market as a whole) over the past 5 years. The formula is covariance of a specfic companies's stock returns and the market stock returns divided by the variance of the market stock returns over the same period.

Name: ivol_ff3_21d
definition: Idiosyncratic volatility (i.e. volatility that cannot be explained by market volatility) from the Fama-French 3-factor model of the previous month)

Name: coskew_21d
definition: measure of coskewness between the error term of the CAPM model and market stock returns over the previous month

Name: resff3_6_1
definition: Residual momentum (error term in Fama-French 3-factor model) over the past 6 months

Name: ivol_hxz4_21d
definition: Idiosyncratic volatility from the q-factor model (i.e. q-factor model is an empirical implementation of the investment-based capital asset pricing model [the Investment CAPM]) of the past 21 tradings (i.e. the preivous month)

Name: iskew_hxz4_21d
definition: Idiosyncratic skewness from the q-factor model (skewness of the error term of the q-factor model)

Name: beta_dimson_21d
definition: Dimson market beta over the previous 21 trading days (i.e. the previous month). A market beta is measure of the volatility–or systematic risk–of a security or portfolio compared to the market as a whole.

Name: betabab_1260d
definition: correlation between the stock returns and the market stock returns for the previous 5 years multiplied by the stock's realized volatility of the previous year divided by the market realized volatility of the previous year.

Name: corr_1260d
definition: correlation between the stock returns and the market stock returns for the previous 5 years

Name: ivol_capm_252d
definition: Idiosyncratic volatility from the CAPM (i.e. Capital Asset Pricing Model) of the past 252 trading days (i.e. the previous year)

Name: rvol_21d
definition: stock returns volatility of the previous trading 21 days (i.e. the previous month)

Name: rskew_21d
definition: Skewness of the stock returns over the previous month (21 trading days)

Name: rmax5_rvol_21d
definition: Maximum 5-day stock returns over the previous 21 trading days (i.e. the previous month) scaled by annual realized volatility (voatility of the stock returns of the past year)

Name: rmax5_21d
definition: Maximum 5-day stock returns over the previous 21 trading days (i.e. the previous month)

Name: rmax1_21d
definition: Maximum daily stock return over the previous 21 trading days (i.e. the previous month)

Name: resff3_12_1
definition: Residual momentum (error term in Fama-French 3-factor model) over the past year

Name: betadown_252d
definition: Beta (i.e. measure of the volatility–or systematic risk–of a security or portfolio compared to the market as a whole) of a stock's stock returns with respect to the negative market stock returns (i.e. when the market stock returns are negative) over the previous year. This is calculated using linear regression.

Name: ivol_capm_21d
definition: Idiosyncratic volatility from the CAPM (i.e. Capital Asset Pricing Model) of the past 21 tradings (i.e. the previous month)
